454
00:21:21,140 --> 00:21:22,030
We meet again.

455
00:21:23,190 --> 00:21:24,070
What a coincidence.

456
00:21:24,380 --> 00:21:25,340
Are you here for me?

457
00:21:27,740 --> 00:21:28,430
Excuse me?

458
00:21:29,030 --> 00:21:31,340
Is this how you treat your client?

459
00:21:36,950 --> 00:21:37,670
Have some water.

460
00:21:45,340 --> 00:21:47,980
You want us to manage,

461
00:21:48,140 --> 00:21:49,670
in a reasonable fashion,

462
00:21:49,980 --> 00:21:51,670
the disposable 5 million yuan you have.

463
00:21:52,670 --> 00:21:54,710
But you do not have any specific requirements

464
00:21:55,380 --> 00:21:56,620
for the risk and the yields.

465
00:21:58,380 --> 00:21:59,790
Your husband

466
00:22:00,030 --> 00:22:01,590
is the president of a financial company.

467
00:22:02,030 --> 00:22:05,790
Your family owns many properties and cars.

468
00:22:06,310 --> 00:22:07,310
And you

469
00:22:07,310 --> 00:22:09,430
are a senior partner in a law firm.

470
00:22:10,380 --> 00:22:12,950
Considering your income level,

471
00:22:13,190 --> 00:22:15,140
I suggest the following distribution.

472
00:22:15,500 --> 00:22:17,950
You have a healthy source of income,

473
00:22:17,980 --> 00:22:19,860
which means high-risk resistance.

474
00:22:20,340 --> 00:22:21,190
I suggest

475
00:22:21,260 --> 00:22:22,460
that 10% of the fund

476
00:22:22,550 --> 00:22:25,620
can be used on volatile assets

477
00:22:25,670 --> 00:22:26,980
such as money market funds.

478
00:22:27,260 --> 00:22:28,790
20%

479
00:22:28,790 --> 00:22:29,460
will go to

480
00:22:29,460 --> 00:22:32,140
the bond fund, which has a lower risk.

481
00:22:32,460 --> 00:22:35,140
Another 30%, that is 1.5 million,

482
00:22:35,260 --> 00:22:37,460
can be placed into a trust fund.

483
00:22:37,590 --> 00:22:38,710
The overall earnings yield

484
00:22:38,710 --> 00:22:40,980
will be around 8% to 10%.

485
00:22:41,140 --> 00:22:42,860
As for the last 40%,

486
00:22:43,500 --> 00:22:46,100
you can look around the primary market.

487
00:22:46,190 --> 00:22:48,260
It's filled with small companies

488
00:22:48,310 --> 00:22:49,910
with good potential that haven't gone public.

489
00:22:49,980 --> 00:22:51,830
I will have my colleagues

490
00:22:52,070 --> 00:22:53,140
explain it to you in detail.

491
00:22:55,790 --> 00:22:56,740
You're a professional.

492
00:22:57,340 --> 00:22:59,460
However, you forgot a crucial element.

493
00:22:59,950 --> 00:23:01,070
Education fund.

494
00:23:02,310 --> 00:23:04,220
My child will be attending
an elementary school next year.

495
00:23:04,590 --> 00:23:07,070
I want a healthy fund for him.

496
00:23:07,260 --> 00:23:08,950
He'll go to the best school

497
00:23:09,190 --> 00:23:10,790
